<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2176">
Your task is to count the number of ways $k$ bishops can be placed on an $n \times n$ chessboard so that no two bishops attack each other.<br />
<br />
Two bishops attack each other if they are on the same diagonal.<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has two integers $n$ and $k$: the board size and the number of bishops.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print one integer: the number of ways modulo $10^9+7$.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 500$<br />
<li>$1 \le k \le n^2$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>5 4</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>2728</code>    </div>
